HEADWORD: Cantref
<hw>Can"tref</hw>, }</mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[W. <ets>cantref</ets>; <ets>cant</ets> hundred +
<ets>tref</ets> dwelling place, village.]</ety> <def>A district
comprising a hundred villages, as in Wales.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>kantry</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
